      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=jx96IN1eFaMAX-Gnctd\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ebc7532302375342179d4b40d10610c9\u0026oe=6025A9FC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3895599693806824\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe season is over, but activists and NFL professional athletes Justin Simmons, Alexander Johnson, and De'Vante Bausby know there is much work to be done off-field. “We are either a nation of ‘we the people’ or ‘we the prisons’ — we can’t be both,” Johnson says in the ad.\"\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.westword.com/news/broncos-players-push-colorado-governor-to-decarcerate-prisons-11880641\"\u003e“Governor Polis, you have the clemency powers to save lives.\"\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQHBHTN6lbEcuJPQ\u0026w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=https%3A%2F%2Fimages1.westword.com%2Fimager%2Fu%2Foriginal%2F11880704%2Fjustin_simmons.png\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_cb=1\u0026_nc_hash=AQHV-S0VVtwuAmCw\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003ewestword.com\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn New Ad, Broncos Players Push Polis to Decarcerate Prisons\u003c/p\u003e“Governor Polis, you have the clemency powers to save lives.\"\u003ca href=\"https://www.westword.com/news/broncos-players-push-colorado-governor-to-decarcerate-prisons-11880641\"\u003e“Governor Polis, you have the clemency powers to save lives.\"\u003c/a\u003e",
