      "url": "https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3873709275995866",
      "title": "Several medical authorities outside and inside Colorado released...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=jx96IN1eFaMAX-Gnctd\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ebc7532302375342179d4b40d10610c9\u0026oe=6025A9FC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3873709275995866\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cp\u003eSeveral medical authorities outside and inside Colorado released guidance on who should have vaccine priority. Against these recommendations, Gov. Polis decided to change Colorado's distribution plan and demoted groups like people experiencing homelessness and those living in congregate settings like jails and prisons. \u003cbr /\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2021/01/02/covid-vaccine-prisons/\"\u003ehttps://www.washingtonpost.com/…/…/02/covid-vaccine-prisons/\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2021/01/02/covid-vaccine-prisons/\"\u003eA shift in Colorado offers an early sign that prisons and jails, which disproportionately hold people of color and have reported some of the most virulent coronavirus outbreaks, are creating daunting dilemmas for state leaders apportioning finite shares of the vaccine.\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?d=AQFyuuKMBIDnjUXu\u0026w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fwp-apps%2Fimrs.php%3Fsrc%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Farc-anglerfish-washpost-prod-washpost.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2FFYVBMMR6HEI6XNMLCYR7MJTZMA.jpg%26w%3D1440\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_cb=1\u0026_nc_hash=AQGoqLT5Zcs8Ium2\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003ewashingtonpost.com\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eEarly vaccination in prisons, a public health priority, proves politically charged\u003c/p\u003eA shift in Colorado offers an early sign that prisons and jails, which disproportionately hold people of color and have reported some of the most virulent coronavirus outbreaks, are creating daunting dilemmas for state leaders apportioning finite shares of the vaccine.\u003ca href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/health/2021/01/02/covid-vaccine-prisons/\"\u003eA shift in Colorado offers an early sign that prisons and jails, which disproportionately hold people of color and have reported some of the most virulent coronavirus outbreaks, are creating daunting dilemmas for state leaders apportioning finite shares of the vaccine.\u003c/a\u003e",
