      "url": "https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3847054248661369",
      "title": "Protecting incarcerated people from COVID-19 is a matter of...",
      "content_html": "\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://scontent.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/v/t31.0-1/cp0/p50x50/21950661_1662566980443451_7358479861831904430_o.jpg?_nc_cat=103\u0026ccb=2\u0026_nc_sid=dbb9e7\u0026_nc_ohc=jx96IN1eFaMAX-Gnctd\u0026_nc_ht=scontent.fapa1-1.fna\u0026tp=27\u0026oh=ebc7532302375342179d4b40d10610c9\u0026oe=6025A9FC\" alt=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/\"\u003eACLU of Colorado\u003c/a\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/acluofcolorado/posts/3847054248661369\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003cp\u003eProtecting incarcerated people from COVID-19 is a matter of science, law, and basic humanity.\u003c/p\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.aclu.org/news/prisoners-rights/incarcerated-people-should-get-priority-access-to-the-covid-19-vaccine-its-the-smart-and-human-thing-to-do/\"\u003eIf officials fail to prioritize incarcerated individuals for the vaccine, we will take them to court.\u003cimg src=\"https://external.fapa1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/safe_image.php?w=540\u0026h=282\u0026url=https%3A%2F%2Fwp.api.aclu.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2FWEB20-Moderna-COVID-Vaccine-SocialShare-1200x628-1.jpg\u0026cfs=1\u0026upscale=1\u0026fallback=news_d_placeholder_publisher\u0026_nc_cb=1\u0026_nc_hash=AQGexTdrCE3XkKwq\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"262\" caption=\"\" /\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003eaclu.org\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eIncarcerated People Should Get Priority Access to the COVID-19 Vaccine. It's the Smart and Human Thing to Do.\u003c/p\u003eIf officials fail to prioritize incarcerated individuals for the vaccine, we will take them to court.\u003ca href=\"https://www.aclu.org/news/prisoners-rights/incarcerated-people-should-get-priority-access-to-the-covid-19-vaccine-its-the-smart-and-human-thing-to-do/\"\u003eIf officials fail to prioritize incarcerated individuals for the vaccine, we will take them to court.\u003c/a\u003e",
